  "prompt": "Professors that have supervised many Chinese graduate students, how many gifts of tea have you received?",
  "response": "The number of tea gifts received by professors who have supervised many Chinese graduate students can vary widely and depends on several factors, including the individual relationships between the professor and their students, cultural practices, and personal preferences. In Chinese culture, it is common to show respect and gratitude through small gifts, and tea is a traditional and appreciated choice.\n\nProfessors who have supervised many Chinese students may receive tea gifts occasionally, especially during important events such as graduations, holidays (like Chinese New Year), or as a token of thanks. However, there is no fixed number, and it ultimately depends on the students' willingness to express their gratitude in this way.\n\nIf you're a professor or considering this as a custom, it's important to appreciate the gesture while also being mindful of institutional policies regarding gift-giving.",
